      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for your help!\nLooking at Item.Ethernet, its description is \"Ethernet card attributes\", which seems to be scoped to Ethernet.\n\nNetwork adapters like the NVIDIA ConnectX series(ConnectX-7, ConnectX-8) support both Ethernet and InfiniBand protocol modes, so Item.Ethernet may not be the best fit. Item.NetworkAdapter represents physical network adapter hardware without being tied to a specific protocol, which seems more appropriate for this use case.\n\nIndeed, Item.NetworkAdapter semantically covers Item.Ethernet, so marking Item.Ethernet as deprecated would make sense. I\u0027ll follow whatever approach upstream prefers — please let me know how you\u0027d like to handle this and I\u0027ll get it done.\nIf my understanding is incorrect, please feel free to correct me. Thanks!",
